{{Infobox Greek deity
| Image   = Apollo ny carlsberg glyptotek.jpg
| Caption = 2nd century  CE Roman statue of Apollo depicting the god's attributes—the lyre and the snake [[Python (mythology)|Python]]
| Name    = Apollo
| God_of  = God of music, poetry, plague, oracles, sun, medicine, light and knowledge
| Abode   = [[Mount Olympus]]
| Symbol  = [[Lyre]], [[Bay Laurel|laurel]] wreath, [[Python (mythology)|python]], [[raven]], bow and arrows
| Consort =
| Parents = [[Zeus]] and [[Leto]]
