The '''American Football Conference''' ('''AFC''') is one of the two [[Conference (sports)|conferences]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). This conference and its counterpart, the [[National Football Conference]] (NFC), currently contain 16 teams each, making up the 32 teams of the NFL.

The American Football Conference originated as the [[American Football League]] (AFL), which joined with the NFL in the [[AFL–NFL merger]] of 1970. As such most of its teams originally played in the AFL, while three others were NFL teams that were added to the AFC to equalize the number of franchises, and another three are more recent expansion teams.

==Current teams==
Since 2002, the AFC has comprised 16 teams, organized into four [[Division (sport)|divisions]] each containing four teams: [[AFC East|East]], [[AFC North|North]], [[AFC South|South]], and [[AFC West|West]].

